            <div type="translation">
                <p>Flee, maintain silence, live a life of contemplative quiet. These are the roots of being without sin and justice.</p> 
            </div>
            <div type="commentary">
                <p>The inscription is identified with a saying of Arsenios from the Apophegmata Patrum (PG 65, 88β) (<bibl><ptr target="#Sacopoulo1966"/>,<citedRange> 97-98</citedRange></bibl>). It is most likely a paraphrase from Paul's First Epistle to Timothy, 6:11, and Second Epistle to Timothy, 2:22.

</p>  
                
